reviews_data.review_text: Stopped at Elysian Brews on my way through Lake Norman and ended up really impressed. Tons of boba choices (even kid-friendly versions), customizable coffee, and everything is made with real care. The baristas and owner were genuinely welcoming, the space is calm with Wi-Fi and outlets for getting work done, and they even have a private room you can reserve. Family-friendly, drive-thru available, and way better than the previous shop that was here. Definitely worth a visit.

I had a wonderful experience at Elysian Brews! We ordered the Dubai Chocolate Strawberries, a taro boba, and a cappuccino — everything was absolutely delicious. The flavors were rich and well-prepared, and each drink felt thoughtfully made. The ambiance was very nice and relaxing, making it a great place to unwind. On top of that, the customer service was awesome — friendly, welcoming, and attentive. Definitely a spot I’d love to visit again!
EPIC place to go if you’re Indy and like good music, great drinks! Baristas there are SOO NICE

It was my first time at this coffee shop yesterday and the ladies were amazing. They were super helpful, service was quick, and I really liked it. I got the white chocolate and cinnamon latte and a blueberry muffin, which was super delicious. I'll definitely be back again.

Ok, being Asian (and probably the only few here around Denver, LOL), I gotta say, I am a HUGE lover of all things bubble tea…. Know all the major chains that’s popped up all over the US.  Moved to Denver over a year ago (from Houston which is HUGE on bubble teas) & have been praying for one of the major well known bubble tea chains to come here. I love Share Tea, naming one of them.

I drove by yesterday & noticed Elysian Brews & was VERY skeptical but happy to finally see a bubble tea joint in the area! So of course I had to try it out. I ordered the classic milk tea with boba & I have to say, I was very pleasantly surprised by the quality of the tea taste itself.  That’s important distinction between a good boba joint v. A low quality.

I give a  7/8 out of 10 for that.  Great job. However, as for the boba itself, not very impressed.  Give it a 4/10.  Besides the tea flavor & quality, boba is a BIG part of what makes the drink. The one I had was very soggy, almost jello like. Not sure if it was because i came around 5pm & the boba has been sitting around too long or that’s just how they make it.  So if I could give some helpful advice, try to fix that. The popular texture of boba should be SOFT & CHEWY, (bouncy like)  not hard, cold or soggy/mushy. There’s an art to making it right.

All in all, i will definitely come back to try the other bubble tea flavors.  Hope they don’t disappoint. Thank you for opening up a location here in Denver finally b/c we sure could use one!  It’s a good option when i can’t make the longer drive to other major bubble tea chains around Charlotte.

Have been coming to Elysian brews for a few weeks now and my partner and I love it! Olivia is the barista we usually look for as she takes great care of us! She’s made sure to adjust anything we’ve needed and is very hospitable! She goes above and beyond. Give her a raise!! Definitely love the board game atmosphere here too. They have a variety of options you and your friends can choose from. We’ll definitely keep coming back for the warm and welcoming service :)
Love the coffee and service is always friendly. I also got coconut milk when I had chai. Loved it.
Good job
The barista was very nice & made me a great tiramisu flavored latte! One of the best coffees I’ve had in the area
Stopped in for coffee and it was genuinely good. Friendly spot, good atmosphere. I’m planning to come back and try the boba next.
Awesome establishment! Great customer service! Highly recommended.
Stopped by the drive thru for my first visit and I am so thrilled with Elysian Brews!  The drinks are amazing and the service is TOP NOTCH!  I'll definitely be back with family and friends.  10/10
Food was very good and the Mango Boba was fantastic!  Very nice service.
I attended the event "Angels to the animals" amazing environment, cool place to work, drink and chill.
I have always wanted to stop by this coffee shop and finally got the chance! Most delish sugar free vanilla caramel latte! The breakfast selections look amazing! Thank you!
I love this place! The drinks are amazing and the staff are so friendly and helpful.
Awesome establishment. My latte was so good. The owners are fantastic at what they do. And I love the gaming aspects too.
Tried this new coffee spot today and got the hot Arctic Spice (white chocolate + gingerbread) — it was really good and nice atmosphere. I’ll definitely be back.
Excellent products and services!!!
Got an Oreo Frappe and coconut boba tea, they were both amazing! So happy Denver got a good boba place! The barista was super nice and friendly. Will definitely be back!

The variety is great and the drinks are so good! Very friendly and accommodating with the patience to let me work thru my drink FOMO. I didn’t feel rushed to decide. Definitely will be a frequent customer!
Love the drinks and the staff is super friendly! They will do thier best to make any drink even if its not on the board!
New business, good drinks, awesome customer service. I got the Golden Spice my husband got the Caramel macchiato! Drinks are made to order. Nice quiet space to get some work done if needed.
Wonderful service

I’m so excited for a good boba place to be open in Denver! They were very sweet and accommodating. You can tell that they are very focused on making customers happy. And the drinks were delicious and a good price. We got a fruit tea and a milk tea and they were both delicious!
This place is the best tea and coffee place that Denver has ever gotten!!! 10/10
